title: Journal of Companion Animal 2013
description: Since its launch in 1995, Companion Animal has grown to become one of the best read subscription veterinary publications for vets wishing to keep up-to-date with practice. A wide range of peer-reviewed articles are featured in each issue, including small animal and exotic practice, and the journal offers a growing range of online CPD units. The format of the articles varies from quick self-assessments through to in-depth certificate level case studies. The surgery articles provide an excellent picture caption format carefully detailing every step of a surgical procedure.
